1.Difference between Scripting Languages and Programming Languages? 
* scripting language is a single threded language loosely coupled and A programming language is a computer language that is used by programmers (developers) to communicate with computers.

2.What is JavaScript and Why we use JavaScript?
* scripting language is a JavaScript (js) is a light-weight object-oriented programming language which is used by several websites for scripting the webpages. It is an interpreted, full-fledged programming language that enables dynamic interactivity on websites when applied to an HTML document.single threded language loosely coupled. 

